Breathwork
Melt away tightness in the body as you relax the mind.
Opening Ceremony
The chakras are the spiritual highway in which vital life force moves -- this power kundalini class combines breathwork, movement, poses and mantras aimed on facilitating a feeling of being aligned and connected.
There are plenty of ways to shortcut your way into a pose, or at least something that looks like the pose on quick inspection, but here we’ll be focusing on integrity over aesthetics. Backbends have countless benefits, if done mindfully, but have lots of less-than-desirable outcomes if you are ‘chasing the shape’. Here, through a controlled vinyasa practice, we’ll be especially looking at; finding evenness, enhancing technique, building strength and finding comfort, in your backbends. We’ll strengthen your over- loose bits and open your over-tight bits. We’ll explore dancers, wheel, cobra, drop backs, bow and plenty more.
And Relax ...
Schedule – February 10–12, 2023 (PDF)
Vinyasa Krama "Open your heart"
Tibetan yoga (Tsa Lung Thrul Khor), sometimes called magical movements, has long been practiced in the Himalayas, both for its health benefits, and for its ability to support spiritual practice and meditation. As opposed to the often more known Hatha yoga, Tibetan yoga has a more dynamic characteristics, with less static holds, and there is an emphasis on specific breath patterns that follow the different movements. In this session you will be guided through a sequence of breath-synchronized movements that aim to remove blockages within the nadis (the energy circuits of the subtle body) and prepare you for the seated meditation at the end.
A moment to slow down, and create space in the body and the mind.
Closing Ceremony
I often describe this specific style of Breathwork as couples therapy between you and you. It is a dynamic and active meditation technique that harnesses the intelligence of the breath, your breath, to help soften the analytical mind while supporting the body and the nervous system in an emotional and energetic release. This practice can leave you feeling deeply grounded, less burdened, authentically you, and more at home within your body.
An authentic Vinyasa Krama practice that is focused, precise and purposeful. Journey through the story of Brahma, the God of creation, one of the three personas of the trimurti as we explore the sequence of grounding, standing, inversions and reclined postures.
Ottilia Bergström – The evulotion of a tree
"Ladder Flow"
Heavenly Hips and Tight bits
In a world where everything is moving fast this practice gives you the opportunity to move slow and take time. Time to connect body and mind, time to adjust, and time to feel and breathe in each pose. At a therapeutic pace Karolin will guide you through a slow flow sequence that stretches and strengthens your entire body in a relaxed atmosphere.
Cold Immersion
Everything starts from something.
For something to then grow into a majestic tree, is quite an impressive process. Similarly, in the same way that a seed can develop into such a remarkable thing as a tree, so can we as humans beings. Join Ottilia in this class to explore the possibilities to find steady ground from where you can move freely. You will be guided through a vinyasa yoga practice, to find strength and flexibility within the concept of yoga - body, mind and soul.
Karolin Axelsson - Slow Flow
