Class desctiption | Varberg Winter Retreat | Asia Spa
At the closing ceremony everyone will gather for a cerimonial experience to end the retreat together. There will also be a Q&A with Michael and some of the teachers for you to ask questions that might have arisen druring the weekend. There will also be a little surprise for everyone. A wonderful event that you don’t want to miss out on.
Activities we do every day, from picking up babies, to hunching over desks can create huge habitual tightness in our bodies.  In this class, via a controlled vinyasa practice with some deeper static sections, we’ll we target those problem areas parts, finding increased flexibility in the stiff bits and strength in the weak bits. Amongst other things, attention will be given to shoulders, chest, hips, legs, and plenty more. Maybe you’ll find a huge sense of release and maybe you’ll find parts especially intense,  but you’ll certainly take home some useful ideas on how you can find more balance in your body, both in class and at home.
There’s a family of asana that every 21st-century body loves and needs, the twists! We’ll begin by touching base on the mechanics of what’s happening in your body when you twist with integrity, then via a controlled vinyasa practice, we’ll gradually explore the core-muscles required for non-levered twist and then begin to add some leavers, gradually getting deeper into our opening and closing twists. We’ll explore adding our new found twists to increasingly challenging balancing poses and arm balances.
In this class you will have the opportunity to connect to your own life force energy - Qi. Jonna guides you into your body, your presence and your own flow of Qi. With movements from Chinese Qigong you support your meridians to let Qi flow freely in your system. Enjoy the opportunity to create soft movements at an almost meditative pace to really sense the sensations in your body. In the end of the class the sounds of Gongs will help you release your system and create even more room for Qi moving freely in your being.
Yin on!


